rect.title: A QuantityKind is a kind of quantity that may be stated by means of defined units.
A QuantityKind is a kind of quantity that may be stated by means of defined units.
A Unit is a quantity in terms of which the magnitudes of other quantities that have the same quantity kind can be stated. A unit often relies on precise and reproducible ways to measure the unit.
